HOUSE BILL 1434
J1, O3, O2 6lr3532
By: Delegate McCaskill
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Health
Committee Report: Favorable
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 9, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Maryland Department of Health – Caregiver Resource Webpage – Establishment
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to develop and maintain
4 a caregiver resource webpage with information and resources to support certain
5 caregivers in the State; and generally relating to a caregiver resource webpage.
6 BY adding to
7 Article – Health – General
8 Section 20–2501 through 20–2503 to be under the new subtitle “Subtitle 25.
9 Caregiver Resource Webpage”
10 Annotated Code of Maryland
11 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
12 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
13 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
14 Article – Health – General
15 SUBTITLE 25. CAREGIVER RESOURCE WEBPAGE.
16 20–2501.
17 IN THIS SUBTITLE:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1434*

2 HOUSE BILL 1434
1 (1) “CAREGIVER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO PROVIDES CARE,
2 SUPERVISION, OR ASSISTANCE TO ANOTHER INDIVIDUAL DUE TO THE INDIVIDUAL’S
3 AGE, DISABILITY, CHRONIC ILLNESS, COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT, OR OTHER
4 FUNCTIONAL LIMITATION;
5 (2) “CAREGIVER” INCLUDES:
6 (I) A PARENT OR GUARDIAN OF A CHILD WITH A DISABILITY,
7 CHRONIC ILLNESS, COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT, OR OTHER FUNCTIONAL LIMITATION;
8 (II) AN INDIVIDUAL CARING FOR AN ADULT FAMILY MEMBER OR
9 LOVED ONE WITH A DISABILITY, CHRONIC ILLNESS, COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT, OR
10 OTHER FUNCTIONAL LIMITATION; AND
11 (III) A MINOR OR DEPENDENT PROVIDING CARE TO A PARENT,
12 GRANDPARENT, OR OTHER ADULT DUE TO THE AGE, DISABILITY, CHRONIC ILLNESS,
13 COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT, OR OTHER FUNCTIONAL LIMITATION OF THE PARENT,
14 GRANDPARENT, OR OTHER ADULT; AND
15 (3) “CAREGIVER” DOES NOT INCLUDE A PARENT OR GUARDIAN
16 PROVIDING CARE, SUPERVISION, OR ASSISTANCE TO A CHILD THAT DOES NOT HAVE
17 A DISABILITY, CHRONIC ILLNESS, COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT, OR OTHER FUNCTIONAL
18 LIMITATION.
19 20–2502.
20 (A) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP AND MAINTAIN A CENTRALIZED
21 CAREGIVER RESOURCE WEBPAGE FOR CAREGIVERS IN THE STATE.
22 (B) THE CAREGIVER RESOURCE WEBPAGE SHALL:
23 (1) BE POSTED IN A CONSPICUOUS LOCATION ON THE DEPARTMENT’S
24 WEBSITE; AND
25 (2) PROVIDE PLAIN–LANGUAGE, EASILY ACCESSIBLE INFORMATION
26 TO SUPPORT ALL TYPES OF CAREGIVERS AT DIFFERENT STAGES OF CAREGIVING.
27 (C) THE CAREGIVER RESOURCE WEBPAGE SHALL INCLUDE INFORMATION
28 AND LINKS TO RESOURCES RELATED TO:
29 (1) CAREGIVING FOR:

HOUSE BILL 1434 3
1 (I) CHILDREN WITH DISABILITIES AND SPECIAL HEALTH CARE
2 NEEDS, INCLUDING EDUCATIONAL AND SCHOOL–BASED SUPPORTS;
3 (II) ADULTS WITH DISABILITIES, CHRONIC ILLNESS, OR
4 BEHAVIORAL HEALTH NEEDS; AND
5 (III) OLDER ADULTS, INCLUDING INDIVIDUALS WITH DEMENTIA
6 OR COGNITIVE IMPAIRMENT;
7 (2) CAREGIVER HEALTH, WELLNESS, AND RESPITE RESOURCES;
8 (3) STATE AND LOCAL PROGRAMS THAT MAY PROVIDE FINANCIAL
9 ASSISTANCE, TRAINING, OR SUPPORT TO CAREGIVERS;
10 (4) SAFETY PLANNING, INCLUDING WANDERING AND ELOPEMENT
11 RISKS; AND
12 (5) PRIVACY, DATA MINIMIZATION, AND DATA SECURITY
13 CONSIDERATIONS WHEN TECHNOLOGY IS USED TO SUPPORT CAREGIVING OR
14 SAFETY.
15 (D) IN DEVELOPING THE WEBPAGE UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
16 SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT SHALL COORDINATE WITH:
17 (1) THE STATE DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION;
18 (2) THE DEPARTMENT OF AGING;
19 (3) THE DEVELOPMENTAL DISABILITIES ADMINISTRATION; AND
20 (4) ANY OTHER RELEVANT STATE OR LOCAL AGENCIES.
21 (E) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL REVIEW AND UPDATE THE WEBPAGE AS
22 NECESSARY, BUT NOT LESS THAN ANNUALLY.
23 20–2503.
24 THIS SUBTITLE MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED TO REQUIRE THE DEPARTMENT, ANY
25 STATE OR LOCAL AGENCY, OR ANY OTHER PERSON DESCRIBED, LISTED, OR LINKED
26 TO ON THE CAREGIVERS RESOURCE WEBPAGE TO PROVIDE OR FUND A SPECIFIC
27 SERVICE, DEVICE, RESOURCE, OR PROGRAM DESCRIBED, LISTED, OR LINKED TO ON
28 THE CAREGIVERS RESOURCE WEBPAGE.

4 HOUSE BILL 1434
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
2 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
